## Early game

**Larzac** on Europa (Dark Sector Defense) is the go-to ground farm: Cubic
Diodes drop from Eximus units on Europa, and Eximus spawns scale up the longer
a Defense runs — the wiki cites 100+ Cubic Diodes by wave 20 here. The Dark
Sector resource drop-chance bonus and Resource Drop Boosters both apply, since
everything comes from enemy drop tables. **Ose** (Interception) is a decent
alternative if you prefer that mission type.

## Mid & late game

Once you have a Railjack, Corpus Proxima is in a different league: Cubic
Diodes are significantly more common in Empyrean than on the Corpus Ice Planet
tileset. End-of-mission bonuses across Venus, Neptune and Pluto Proxima can
award 200 Cubic Diodes at once, and sweeping the storage containers at points
of interest like **Nu-gua Mines** (Neptune Proxima) stacks more on top —
container and mission-reward payouts, so drop boosters don't help there.

